        {
            "review_id": "225634374",
            "steam_id": "76561198198320922",
            "playtime_minutes": 6458,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "I have never been addicted to any video game like this app. After the first 100 hours, I feel like I’m just getting started. I am in love with creating pixel art. This application is by far the best I have found for my general use case. It has everything a person could ask for when creating pixel art. The animation tools are by far the best compared to any other app. I highly recommend it."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "225504782",
            "steam_id": "76561199021468308",
            "playtime_minutes": 631,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Really fun experience for making pixel art. I have not had any issues regarding crashes or file corruptions so far. As an artist its quite fun to use and it poses a challenge to think creatively in a very limited pixel range! I also love how you can make retro style art with it since you can work with 8, 16, & 32 pixel bit canvas sizes."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "225439808",
            "steam_id": "76561198155970048",
            "playtime_minutes": 21503,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Has all the features pixel art needs, and is a generally great app that deserves your money. Anything pixel-art related can be done here, ranging from sprites to animation.\r\n\r\nHowever, I do have some gripes with the layer UI though, as it's very annoying to navigate through. Often than not moving the layers around doesn't really do what you think it does. Sometimes you will override your layers, sometimes you choose the wrong layer, sometimes you won't be able to move the layer on top of other layers, and it goes on and on.\r\n\r\nSometimes you should just take an existing design that works for everyone and just use that, instead of trying to come up with a mediocre solution to a solved problem.\r\n\r\nOther than that - it's pretty good."
        },
