            "review_text": "This software is such a life saver when it comes to making pixel art. Unlike free art softwares out there, making pixel art has always been a struggle. Lacking color consistency with palettes has no longer been a struggle. The animator is very user-friendly too if you're working with sprites.\n\nThe only downside to this software is when you're working with layers... unlike other art programs, it doesn't give you an easier-to-notice indicator that you're on a wrong layer. Honestly that could be a me issue, but it's been more frequent with Aseprite in specific. When it comes to animation, it's hard to differentiate whether or not you're editing the layer for all frames or one frame in specific, it caused me many slip ups."
        },
